Beginner’s Guide To Base Makeup ✨

Episode 9: Setting Spray- this is the final and last step in your makeup routine, it is vvv important to set your makeup so that it stays in place and do not move. 
Tip- if your skin feels dry, you apply your concealer or foundation and spray your setting spray, then blend. It will look super smooth.

See you guys in my next series. I hope you liked it and learnt something new!💕

#macfixplus #settingspray #flawlessmakeup #flawlessbase #explore

Beginner’s guide to base makeup

Episode 8: Highlighter ✨

I used to love love love highlighters in the past but these days i like to use a strobe cream and tints more not like i have stopped applying it fully, i do ofc but i have my days for that lol.

Beginner’s Guide To Base Makeup ✨

Episode 7: Blush💕

Blushes are my FAVVV. I think you can never go wrong w a blush, always choose a shade that you feel suits you the most. There’s nothing like TOO MUCH when it comes to a blush. I love tints, i feel they look super fresh and stay a lil longer.✨

✨ retails for ₹650 

Overall my experience using these eye pencils was greatt, they will be in travel makeup pouch for sure. If you’re looking for coloured eye pencils to creat fun looks, then this should be your pick!💕

These blushes from @mruchabeauty are 🫶🏻✨
The shade range is stunning, from fair to deeper skin tones they got you covered, i want them in all the shades honestly.❤️

Yes, they are expensive not gonna lie, but these blushes are highly pigmented so you need very less product to work with, little goes a long wayyy! I love how beautifully they sit on the face, they are not extremely dewy or matte, somewhere in between, leaving a blurry finish✨🫶🏻

Shades mentioned-
💕Petal
🍑Peachy pop
🍇Mulberry magic
